    <td><strong><font face="Arial" size="4"><b>REFERRAL DETAIL</b></font></strong><font
    face="Times New Roman" size="3"><p>The Referral Detail Report is an explanation of the
    donor referral call. The report is divided into five sections, <i>Caller Information,
    Patient Information, Approach Information, Options <font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><font
    face="Times New Roman" size="3">and Event Log Information. </i>Each Referral Detail Report
    will indicate the Statline referral call number, call date/time, referral type, the
    Statline Triage Coordinator and the status of the referral.</font></font></p>
    <p>The Referral Detail Report documents the actual phone call. <b>The information obtained
    during the referral call depends on the service level that was chosen to meet your
    organization&#146;s needs.</b><u><i></p>
    <p></i><strong>Caller Information</u></strong><br>
    <font face="Times New Roman" size="3">The caller&#146;s first and last name, title and
    sub-location (ex: ER, SICU, OR) will be documented. The organization and phone number
    (with area code) is documented in this section as well.</font></p>
    <u><i><p></i><strong>Patient Information</u></strong><br>
    <font face="Times New Roman" size="3">This section documents the patient demographic
    information. The information is straight forward and documents the patient name, admit
    date to the hospital, gender, age, weight, race, medical record number, ventilator status,
    declaration of death including date and cause of death, case history and past medical
    history (if known at the time of the call). If specific questions were customized for the
    region, positive answers will be documented in the medical information section. </font></p>
    <u><i><p></i><strong>Approach Information</u></strong><br>
    <font face="Times New Roman" size="3">If Statline tracks approach information, this is the
    section that will document the information received from the caller. This section will
    indicate if an approach was done. If an approach was done, the name of who approached the
    family will be documented. Two different types of approaches will be documented. If the
    family was approached about donation options <i>before</i> calling Statline for the
    appropriate options, the approach will be labeled Pre-Referral. If the family was
    approached about donation options <i>after</i> calling Statline for the appropriate
    options, the approach will be labeled Post- Referral. The approach will also be described
    as either a coupled or a decoupled approach. A coupled approach is defined as a discussion
    of death and offering the option of donation at the same time and if the family has not
    come to terms with the death. A decoupled approach is defined as a discussion of death
    separate from a discussion of donation options and the family has come to terms with the
    death. The coupled and decoupled approaches will be documented with the Pre and Post
    Referral status.</font></p>
    <p>The next of kin, relationship and phone number will be documented in this section if
    this information is available from the caller.</p>
    <u><i><p></i><strong>Options</u></strong><br>
    <font face="Times New Roman" size="3">This section will track what donation options are
