    </center></div><u><i><p><br>
    </i><strong>Event Log Information</u></strong><br>
    Every Referral Detail report will contain an event log at the bottom of the page. This
    section tells the story of the referral. For each event type, the date/time, event type,
    organization, to/from, and a description will be documented if applicable. Events that may
    occur during a referral call are the following:</p>
    <blockquote>
      <p><strong><em>Incoming Call</em></strong> - This event is automatically noted on every
      incoming call into the communications center.</p>
      <p><strong><em>Note</em></strong> - This is a brief note if any additional explanation is 
      needed about the referral.  It is also used to describe a floor location if that floor/unit 
      is not included in Statline’s standardized list..</p>
      <p><em><strong>Outgoing Call</strong></em> - The Statline Triage Coordinator will place an
      outgoing call to the appropriate person.</p>
      <p><strong><em>Page Pending</em></strong> - The Statline Triage Coordinator pages the
      appropriate person to relay the message.</p>
      <p><strong><em>Page Response</em></strong> - The Statline Triage Coordinator receives a
      response from the page pending event.</p>
      <p><strong><em>No Page Response</em></strong> - The Statline Triage Coordinator documents
      that a response from the page pending event has not occurred.</p>
      <p><em><strong>Consent Pending</strong></em> - The Statline Triage Coordinator creates a
      consent pending once options have been give on an appropriate donor. The creation of this
      event allows the computer to notify the Triage Coordinator after 4 hours to follow up with
      the hospital if the communications center has not received a call back from the hospital
      (this will only happen if the hospital does the approach for donation).</p>
      <p><strong><em>Consent Outcome</em></strong> - The outcome of the approach is documented. </p>
      <p><em><strong>Recovery Pending</strong></em> - If a family has consented to donation, a
      recovery pending is created until the communications center is notified of the recovery by
      the recovery agency.</p>
      <p><em><strong>Recovery Outcome</strong></em> - The recovery agency has notified the
      communications center of the final outcome of the referral for tracking purposes.</p>
    </blockquote>
